title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV! title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV!  Visit http://autoportal.com/ to know more about different cars, their reviews, price, comparisons and much more. title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV! title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV! title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV! title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. Read More http://www.autoblog.com/2017/02/09/2018-hyunda-elantra-gt-2839237827/  Test Drive Review ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV!  Visit http://autoportal.com/ to know more about different cars, their reviews, price, comparisons and much more. title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV! title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. Read More http://www.autoblog.com/2017/02/09/2018-hyunda-elantra-gt-2839237827/  Test Drive Review ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV! title: 2018 Hyundai Azera - interior Exterior and Drive
description: "The 2018 Hyundai Azera looks pretty classy   With the reveal of the new Azera, Hyundai has made it clear that it has no plans to leave the large, upscale sedan market. This South Korean Avalon-fighter underwent a significant redesign inside and out and will first go on sale in Korea next month.  Outside, the Azera has a significantly different and more formal, profile. While the previous model was rakish and wedgy, the new model adopts an upright version of Hyundai's new corporate grille, along with a long hood and more vertical windshield. The flanks also receive long, flowing character lines that give it a muscular appearance. At the back, the Azera gets a new version of the full width taillights that the model has had since the nameplate's introduction two generations ago.  The Azera also changes radically inside. Instead of the downward flowing dash of the old model, the new interior features an instrument panel that emphasizes width, with a dark top portion and lighter lower section. Sandwiched between the two halves of the dash is a section that rises up at the center stack to house the large touch screen and an analog clock, which looks a bit out of place.  Hyundai has yet to reveal any stats, pricing or availability for the new Azera, except for its aforementioned launch date in South Korea, where it will carry the Grandeur name. However, we would imagine more details will be coming soon ahead of its US launch. Read more http://www.autoblog.com/2016/10/27/2018-hyundai-azera-redesign-style/  ""2017 Test Drive Review""  ""SUBSCRIBE NOW"""

title: 2017 Hyundai i30 - Perfect Car!!
description: "Hyundai i30 comes to America as the 2018 Elantra GT   At last year's Paris Auto Show, Hyundai revealed its clean and classy i30 hatchback, with the promise that it would arrive in the US as the Elantra GT. The company has fulfilled that promise and then some, bringing us the same attractive hatch, but with even more power.  Visually and structurally, the car is pretty much identical. The lines aren't fussy, and the look is more upright than its predecessor. The interior is reasonably attractive, but we wish the infotainment display was better integrated with the dash like the Elantra sedan's dash.   The big differences are under the hood. The European i30 features an array of gas and diesel engines, and the most potent of which produced only about 140 horsepower. In the United States, the least powerful Elantra GT is the naturally aspirated 2.0-liter inline-4 that makes 162 horsepower. And if that's not enough, a Sport version will be offered with Hyundai's 201-horsepower turbocharged 1.6-liter.  The Elantra GT Sport, like its sedan counterpart, also picks up a few other improvements. It trades in the standard hatch's torsion bar rear suspension for a multi-link set-up. It also moves up to 18-inch alloy wheels, instead of the standard 17-inch alloys, and larger front and rear disc brakes. The interior gets some sportier accoutrements, too.   All Elantra GTs will be available with a number of premium options, including leather, dual-zone climate control, cruise control with start and stop functionality, automatic emergency braking, and lane keeping assist. You'll also be able to use Hyundai's Blue Link Alexa feature. Interested buyers will be able to check out an Elantra GT at dealer lots this summer, but Hyundai has not yet released pricing. title: Hyundai NEXO - Because of you
description: El nuevo NEXO es para aquellos que les gusta cargar la batería de su coche en 5 minutos, para los que les gusta respirar aire puro, para los que buscan una vida más fácil y que los suyos vivan en un lugar mejor.  Hemos creado en nuevo Hyundai NEXO porque no somos nada sin ti.  Es un SUV de pila de combustible único. Combina la tecnología más avanzada con un diseño futurista y una increíble autonomía.   El Hyundai NEXO se caracteriza por un diseño puro en el que destaca su silueta aerodinámica y su techo flotante. El frontal, de superficies fluidas, remarca una imagen ancha y claramente definida, con luces diurnas tipo led colocadas en posición horizontal. La rejilla en cascada se ha ampliado para aumentar la entrada de aire, mientras que en los laterales encontramos los primeros tiradores integrados de Hyundai. El objetivo es conseguir un diseño más limpio y mejorar el flujo de aire. El diseño distintivo de la carrocería se traslada al interior, donde encontramos un ancho frontal en el que sobresalen dos pantallas. La primera, de 12,3 pulgadas, contiene la información del sistema de navegación, mientras que la segunda, de 7 pulgadas, conforma la instrumentación digital; muestra la velocidad, el nivel de combustible y la eficiencia de conducción.  Pero lo realmente sorprendente del NEXO es su sistema de propulsión. Monta un motor eléctrico de 120 kW de potencia (equivalente a 163 CV), con un par de 395 Nm. Es capaz de acelerar de 0 a 100 km/h en 9,2 segundos y de alcanzar una velocidad máxima de 179 km/h. Más allá de sus prestaciones, el NEXO destaca por ofrecer una autonomía de 800 kilómetros por depósito, según el test de homologación NEDC. Esto se debe a su excelente eficiencia energética, del 60%, la mejor del mundo. Los ingenieros de Hyundai han trabajado para garantizar que pueda operar sin restricciones en condiciones climatológicas extremas. Así, es capaz de arrancar con temperaturas por debajo de -30ºC y mostrar un excelente rendimiento de refrigeración con temperaturas superiores a 49 ºC.  Este todocamino, además, será el encargado de estrenar algunas de las últimas tecnologías de asistencia a la conducción desarrolladas por Hyundai. Una de ellas es el nuevo monitor de ángulo muerto (Blind-spot View Monitor BVM), un sistema que no sólo alerta de la presencia de otros coches en los puntos ciegos del vehículo, sino que por primera vez en la industria automovilística muestra imágenes de lo que sucede a su alrededor a través de una pantalla situada en el cuadro de instrumentos. Para ello utiliza un sistema de cámaras gran angular en los laterales y en la trasera.  Otro de los avances tecnológicos es el asistente de mantenimiento de carril (Lane Following Assist LFA), que es capaz de realizar correcciones en la dirección de manera autónoma para garantizar que el vehículo se mantenga dentro de su propio carril. Este sistema funciona a velocidades de hasta 145 km/h. El dispositivo, además, se puede combinar con el Highway Driving Assist (HDA), un control de crucero adaptativo que utiliza sensores y datos cartográficos para mejorar el confort a bordo, la seguridad y la autonomía.  El Hyundai NEXO ofrecerá también un sistema de aparcamiento autónomo conocido como Remote Smart Parking Assist (RSPA). Gracias a él, el vehículo puede estacionar o salir de la plaza de aparcamiento en batería sin necesidad de que el conductor se encuentre en el interior del coche. De esta forma, el vehículo podrá realizar la maniobra de manera 100% autónoma mientras el conductor esté fuera con el mando en la mano.  ¡Sigue todas nuestras novedades!  ➡ Nuestra web: http://www.hyundai.es  ➡ Hyundai Experience: http://www.hyundai.es/experience ➡ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Hyundai.es ➡ Twitter: https://twitter.com/HyundaiEsp ➡ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/hyundaiesp

title: Hyundai Creta Test Drive Review - Auto Portal
description: Hyundai Creta : https://autoportal.com/newcars/hyundai/creta/  Hyundai Creta was possibly the most anticipated products of the year and we recently drove the compact SUV. Ashish Masih tests it for us. It is launched in one of the highly competitive segment of the compact SUVs among the rivals like the Ford Ecosport and the Renault Duster. Hyundai Creta comes in a premium price range of Rs 9.22 Lakhs to Rs 14.57 Lakhs (Ex. Showroom, New Delhi). Hyundai has introduced the SUV in both petrol and diesel fuel trims. It can be availed in five variants in gasoline trim: E, E+, SX+ Manual, SX+ Manual Spl Edition and SX+ Automatic. On the other hand, the diesel variants are presented with two powertrains in a total of 9 variants: E, S, S+, SX, SX+, S+ Automatic, SX+ Spl Edition, SX (O), and SX+ Automatic. Needless to say, Hyundai Creta gets all the bells and whistles that one would have wished. On the safety front, it gets several premium and reliable features such as side and curtain airbags, Electronic Stability Control (ESC), Vehicle Stability Management control (VSM), Hill Start Assist Control (HAC), Rear parking camera, Lane Change Flash Adjustment and Speed sensing Auto Door lock. As for comfort and convenience, the SUV comes loaded with a plethora of exquisite features like automatic A/C with ion cluster, rear centre armrest with cup holders, electric tailgate release, height adjustable driver's seat, 7-inch touchscreen AVN system with 1 GB internal memory and bluetooth connectivity, etc. to name a few.  While the Creta has already received a rave response, the Maruti Suzuki S-Cross could play a spoilsport once launched. So, here's our video review of the Hyundai Creta compact SUV!
